SPECIALTY RETAILERS (OTS)
</IN>
<LP>
   K mart Corp. said it agreed to acquire a 22% stake in
OfficeMax Inc., an office supply chain that will purchase K
mart's own smaller office supply operation. Terms weren't
disclosed.
   The Troy, Mich., retailer said that OfficeMax will run its
five Office Square stores, continuing the company's planned
expansion. OfficeMax, a privately held Cleveland company with
projected sales of $250 million for fiscal 1991, operates 34
stores in seven states. By the end of the current fiscal
year, OfficeMax hopes to have about 65 stores.
</LP>
