<HL>
   Business Brief -- Keithley Instruments Inc.:
   Company to Market a Line
   Made by Japan's NF Corp.
</HL>
<DATE>
09/14/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A9B
</SO>
<CO>
   KEI
</CO>
<IN>
ELECTRICAL COMPONENTS AND EQUIPMENT (ELQ)
</IN>
<LP>
   Keithley Instruments Inc. said it agreed to market in
North America a line of measurement instruments produced by
NF Corp. of Japan that will complement its own devices.
   Keithley said the move not only represents a major
addition of product technology and potential sales volume,
but also is expected to increase its own sales of instruments
as well.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Keithley, based in Cleveland, produces measurement
instruments that are used in direct current, or DC,
applications. NF's line of instruments measure in alternating
current, or AC.
   The agreement is effective immediately, subject to
additional negotiations to be completed within 60 days,
Keithley said.
</TEXT>
